TITLE: Implementing Apiato Action with Multiple Tasks (PHP)
DESCRIPTION: Example of an Apiato Action class demonstrating how to inject and orchestrate multiple Task dependencies (`DemoATask`, `DemoBTask`) within the `run` method. It shows how to pass parameters to the Tasks and process their potential results.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apiato/documentation/blob/master/docs/components/main-components/actions.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use ...
use App\Ship\Parents\Actions\Action as ParentAction;

class DemoAction extends ParentAction
{
    public function __construct(
        private readonly DemoATask $demoATask,
        private readonly DemoBTask $demoBTask
    ) {
    }

    public function run($xxx, $yyy, $zzz): void
    {
        $foo = $this->demoATask->run($xxx, $yyy);
        $bar = $this->demoBTask->run($zzz);
    }
}
```

