TITLE: Creating a Basic API Controller in Apiato (PHP)
DESCRIPTION: Shows a sample PHP class for an API Controller. It must extend `App\Ship\Parents\Controllers\ApiController`, injects a specific request object (`RegisterUserRequest`), calls the `run` method of an Action (`RegisterUserAction`) passing the request, and uses the `transform` helper to format the response using a specified `UserTransformer`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apiato/documentation/blob/master/versioned_docs/version-11.x/main-components/controllers.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
class Controller extends ApiController
{
    public function registerUser(RegisterUserRequest $request)
    {
        $user = app(RegisterUserAction::class)->run($request);
        return $this->transform($user, UserTransformer::class);
    }
}
```

