TITLE: Defining a Protected GET Route with Middleware in Laravel (PHP)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to define a GET route in Laravel that is protected by authentication middleware. The route responds to 'users' endpoint requests and delegates them to the 'listAllUsers' method on the Controller class, only allowing authenticated API users to access this endpoint. Laravel's routing system and the 'auth:api' middleware are required dependencies. Input is an HTTP GET request from authenticated clients, and the output is provided by the controller method. Ensure the middleware is properly configured in the Laravel app for this to work.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apiato/documentation/blob/master/versioned_docs/version-11.x/main-components/routes.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: php
