TITLE: Create Admin Action Sample in Apiato (PHP)
DESCRIPTION: This code defines an Action to create an admin user. It uses Tasks to create the user with credentials and assign the 'admin' role. The `run` method takes email, password, name, and an optional isClient flag as input, and returns the created User object. It depends on `CreateUserByCredentialsTask` and `AssignUserToRoleTask`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apiato/documentation/blob/master/versioned_docs/version-11.x/main-components/actions.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
class CreateAdminAction extends Action
{
    public function run(string $email, string $password, string $name, bool $isClient = false): User
    {
        $admin = app(CreateUserByCredentialsTask::class)->run(
            $isClient,
            $email,
            $password,
            $name
        );

        app(AssignUserToRoleTask::class)->run($admin, ['admin']);

        return $admin;
    }
}
```

