TITLE: Defining a Task Class in PHP (Apiato)
DESCRIPTION: Example of a Task class (`FindUserByIdTask`) in Apiato. It extends the base `Task` class, injects a `UserRepository` dependency via the constructor, and defines a `run` method to execute the core logic (finding a user by ID). Includes basic error handling by catching exceptions and throwing a specific `UserNotFoundException`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apiato/documentation/blob/master/versioned_docs/version-10.x/main-components/tasks.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
class FindUserByIdTask extends Task
{
    private $userRepository;

    public function __construct(UserRepository $userRepository)
    {
        $this->userRepository = $userRepository;
    }

    public function run($id)
    {
        try {
            $user = $this->userRepository->find($id);
        } catch (Exception $e) {
            throw new UserNotFoundException();
        }

        return $user;
    }
}
```

