TITLE: Creating a Laravel Migration in Apiato
DESCRIPTION: PHP code example demonstrating a Laravel migration class (`CreateDemoTable`) within an Apiato container. It defines the `up` method to create a 'demos' table with standard columns (id, timestamps, softDeletes) using the Schema builder, and the `down` method to drop the table.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apiato/documentation/blob/master/versioned_docs/version-11.x/optional-components/migrations.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
class CreateDemoTable extends Migration
{
    public function up()
    {
        Schema::create('demos', function (Blueprint $table) {
            $table->increments('id');
            // ...
            $table->timestamps();
            $table->softDeletes();
        });
    }

    public function down()
    {
        Schema::drop('demos');
    }
}
```

