TITLE: Defining a Mail Class with Laravel Mail and Queueing in PHP
DESCRIPTION: This PHP snippet defines a mail notification class named UserRegisteredMail which extends the base Mail class and implements ShouldQueue, enabling queueing of email sending jobs. It uses the Queueable trait for dispatching to queues. The constructor accepts a User object which is stored for use in the build method. The build method configures the email view template, recipient address and name, and passes user data to the view. Dependencies include Laravel's mail system, ShouldQueue interface, and Queueable trait. Inputs are a User instance; outputs are the built mail ready for sending or queueing.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apiato/documentation/blob/master/versioned_docs/version-10.x/optional-components/mails.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
class UserRegisteredMail extends Mail implements ShouldQueue
{
    use Queueable;

    protected $user;

    public function __construct(User $user)
    {
        $this->user = $user;
    }

    public function build()
    {
        return $this->view('appSection@user::user-registered')
            ->to($this->user->email, $this->user->name)
            ->with([
                'name' => $this->user->name,
            ]);
    }
}
```

