TITLE: Defining a Criteria Accepting Data (PHP)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates how to create a Criteria class that accepts data via its constructor. The accepted data (a user ID in this case) is stored and then used within the `apply` method to build a dynamic query condition (filtering records by the specified user ID). This allows for more flexible and data-driven criteria.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apiato/documentation/blob/master/versioned_docs/version-10.x/optional-components/criterias.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
class ThisUserCriteria extends Criteria
{
    private $userId;

    public function __construct($userId)
    {
        $this->userId = $userId;
    }

    public function apply($model, PrettusRepositoryInterface $repository)
    {
        return $model->where('user_id', '=', $this->userId);
    }
}
```

