TITLE: Defining an Apiato Transporter Class in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Example of a Transporter class (`ProxyApiLoginTransporter`) extending the base `Transporter`. It defines a schema with properties, required fields, and default values using the `$schema` property, leveraging the underlying DTO package.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apiato/documentation/blob/master/versioned_docs/version-9.x/main-components/transporters.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

namespace App\Containers\Authentication\Transporters;

use App\Ship\Parents\Transporters\Transporter;

class ProxyApiLoginTransporter extends Transporter
{

    /**
     * @var array
     */
    protected $schema = [
