TITLE: Implementing FindUserByIdTask - PHP
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines a `FindUserByIdTask` class that extends the base `Task` class. It utilizes a `UserRepository` to search for a user by their ID. The `run` method attempts to find the user, throwing a `UserNotFoundException` if the user isn't found and returning the user if found. The constructor receives a `UserRepository` instance and assigns it to a private property for later use. This task exemplifies retrieving a user by ID using repository pattern within the architecture.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apiato/documentation/blob/master/versioned_docs/version-11.x/main-components/tasks.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
```php
class FindUserByIdTask extends Task
{
    private $userRepository;

    public function __construct(UserRepository $userRepository)
    {
        $this->userRepository = $userRepository;
    }

    public function run($id)
    {
        try {
            $user = $this->userRepository->find($id);
        } catch (Exception $e) {
            throw new UserNotFoundException();
        }

        return $user;
    }
}
```
```

