TITLE: Allowing addRequestCriteria Invocation in Repository Mock - Apiato Core (PHP)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to allow invocation of the addRequestCriteria method on a repository mock when testing features that utilize RequestCriteria. The test uses assertCriteriaPushedToRepository to set expectations for repository interactions, and allowAddRequestCriteriaInvocation enables the stub method on the mock object. Dependencies include an instance of UserRepository, UserIsAdminCriteria, and ListUsersTask. The method streamlines repository-testing when criteria are involved, especially for admin-related filtering logic.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apiato/documentation/blob/master/docs/components/optional-components/tests.md#_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
public function testCanListAdminUsers(): void
{
    $repositoryMock = $this->assertCriteriaPushedToRepository(
        UserRepository::class,
        UserIsAdminCriteria::class,
        ['admin' => true],
    );
    // highlight-next-line
    $this->allowAddRequestCriteriaInvocation($repositoryMock);
    $task = app(ListUsersTask::class);

    $task->admin();
}
```

