TITLE: Defining a custom Value Object class in PHP
DESCRIPTION: This PHP code defines a custom Value Object class 'Location' that extends the base Value class from APIATO. It encapsulates coordinate data with private properties, a constructor for initialization, and a method to return coordinates as a formatted string. The class demonstrates typical usage of Value Objects to represent immutable data structures.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apiato/documentation/blob/master/versioned_docs/version-9.x/optional-components/values.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
<?php

use App\Ship\Parents\Values\Value;

class Location extends Value
{
    private $x = null;

    private $y = null;

    protected $resourceKey = 'locales';

    public function __construct($x, $y)
    {
        $this->x = $x;
        $this->y = $y;
    }

    public function getCoordinatesAsString()
    {
        return $this->x . ' - ' . $this->y;
    }
}

```

