TITLE: API Endpoint DocBlock Example
DESCRIPTION: Example of a DocBlock for documenting an API endpoint. It includes information like the API group, name, method, description, version, permissions, headers, parameters, and success/error responses.  These DocBlocks must be written in the Routes files to be loaded by the documentation generator.
SOURCE: https://github.com/apiato/documentation/blob/master/versioned_docs/version-12.x/pacakges/documentation.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: php
